The humble petition of Richard Cromwell, late Lord Protector of England, Scotland, and Ireland, to the councel of officers at Walingford House.
1 sheet ([1] p.)
s.n., [London : 1659]
Not in fact by Richard Cromwell, but rather a satire on him. Imprint from Wing. Annotation on Thomason copy: "xber [i.e., December]. 27 1659". Reproductions of the originals in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery (Early English books) and the British Library (Thomason Tracts).
